In 2018, the proof of this success came in for the Greek chapter, where, for almost half a century, Greece was the benefactor of the community. It adopted strategies and practices from successful countries in the fields of security or healthcare, for instance. The rich world adopted Europe. But, in recent years, we’ve seen two different kinds of economies in Europe.

Some have had better policies and have managed to emerge from the crisis much more quickly, whether western powers like Germany or the Club Med south, consisting of Greece, Spain, Portugal and Ireland. This saysthe countries with effective management of the economy that are able to regain their status and their rights.Today, Greece is, for economic reasons and because of lack of infrastructure, in a genetic disadvantage position that it will take many years to change. But Greece has made progress since the crisis has given it a wake-up call. Currently, there is talk of a business continuity plan throughout Europe. In this scenario, Greece, northern Europe and European powers such as Germany are in favor of an orderly withdrawal of Britain.
